'''''From Abjection to Alchemy: Tolkien's Middle-earth Legendarium''''' is the title of Sara Brown's PhD thesis, presented at the [[Wikipedia:University of Salford|University of Salford]].<ref>{{webcite|author=|articleurl=http://uk.linkedin.com/pub/dr-sara-brown/12/220/b61|articlename=Dr Sara Brown|dated=|website=[http://uk.linkedin.com/ UK.Linkedin.com]|accessed=19 September 2013}}</ref>

For the work on her thesis, Brown was permitted access to [[J.R.R. Tolkien]]'s private papers held at the [[Bodleian Library]]: "''There she was able to study transcripts of lectures and drafts of some of Tolkien's essays and literary works, including a small note in the author's handwriting ... concerning the character of Gandalf''".<ref>{{webcite|author=|articleurl=http://rydalpenrhos.com/news/13/04/lifelong_passion_for_tolkien|articlename=Lifelong passion for Tolkien|dated=April 2013|website=[http://rydalpenrhos.com/ Rydalpenrhos.com]|accessed=19 September 2013}}</ref>

